# 🧠 Virtual Memory – Psychologically Retention Notes (OS)

---

## 🌟 CORE IDEA
- Virtual memory makes the computer feel like it has MORE RAM than actual RAM
- It uses **RAM + Disk (swap space)** together
- Disk is NOT converted into RAM → it is only used as backup storage

🧠 Memory Trick:  
👉 “Fake big memory using real RAM + slow disk backup”

---

## 📦 MEMORY ORGANIZATION

### 🧩 RAM Structure
- RAM is divided into fixed-size blocks → **Frames**

### 📄 Program Structure
- Program is divided into same-size blocks → **Pages**

👉 1 Page = 1 Frame (size-wise)

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Pages live in Frames”

---

## 🗺️ PAGE TABLE (BRAIN OF SYSTEM)
- Each process has a **Page Table**
- It maps:
  👉 Page → Frame location in RAM

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Page Table = Address Map of memory”

---

## ⚙️ MMU (TRANSLATOR MACHINE)
- MMU converts:
  👉 Virtual Address → Physical Address

🧠 Trick:
👉 “MMU = Language converter of memory”

---

## ⚡ TLB (FAST MEMORY BOOST)
- TLB stores **recent address translations**
- Works like a cache for MMU

🧠 Trick:
👉 “TLB = Memory shortcut box 🚀”

---

## 📥 DEMAND PAGING
- Only required pages are loaded into RAM
- Not full program loading

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Bring only needed pages, not whole book”

---

## ❌ PAGE FAULT
- Happens when required page is NOT in RAM

👉 OS must:
- Go to disk
- Bring page into RAM

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Page missing = Page Fault alarm 🚨”

---

## 🔁 SWAPPING
- Happens when RAM is full
- OS removes old page → adds new page

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Out with old, in with new”

---

## 📊 PAGE REPLACEMENT ALGORITHMS
Used when choosing which page to remove:
- FIFO (First In First Out)
- LRU (Least Recently Used)

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Oldest or least used gets kicked out”

---

## 🧽 DIRTY BIT (CHANGE TRACKER)
- Dirty bit = page modified or not

- 1 → modified → must write back to disk ✏️  
- 0 → not modified → no need to save

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Dirty = changed = must clean (save)”

---

## 🔒 PROTECTION BITS (SECURITY LAYER)
Controls access rights:
- Read 📖
- Write ✍️
- Execute ⚙️
- Restricted (OS only) 🔐

🧠 Trick:
👉 “Who can touch memory and how”

---

## 🔥 ONE-LINE SUPER REVISION
👉 Pages map to frames → MMU translates → TLB speeds → page fault loads → swapping manages space → dirty bit saves changes → protection bits secure memory

---

## 🧠 FINAL MEMORY HOOK
👉 “Load smart (demand paging), translate fast (MMU+TLB), fix missing (page fault), replace old (swapping), save changes (dirty bit), protect access (protection bits)”